data.message: Is there anyone who can help me?  I have lost my News Feed Page.   My News Feed is completely blank....   I have No Posts, Groups, Games, Messages, or lists.  I have tried refreshing and restarting my computer but nothing is working.  I have reloaded my Adobe and Flash Player and nothing is working. Can someone please help me?  I can't even do a search or pull down messages from the top if I am on the News Feed screen.  I can only access my Timeline.      :(

replies.message: Hey Michele. Your News Feed should be filled with updates from your friends and people and Pages you follow. If you've tried refreshing your page and it's still blank, let us know: https://www.facebook.com/help/186570224871049 Thanks! -Hailey
I did report the problem a few hours ago.  Should I do it again?
Thanks, Michele. Please sit tight while we take the time to review the situation. We appreciate your patience! -Rose
I had the very same problem and no one responded to my concern.
We see, Stacey. If your News Feed is still blank even after you've refreshed it, please let us know here: http://on.fb.me/1AoZhtZ. Thank you! -Rose
Clean out you temporary Internet files and cookies!
Julie I had done that already (Out of habit I actually do that every day).  It was a facebook issue.  They finally did fix it for me.  When I woke up this morning my account was back to normal.  ;)
